  "text": "The present study is limited because we could not measure the sensory regression time of spinal block because all patients were moderately sedated (BIS <85). A previously study reported that intravenous dexmedetomidine prolonged the duration of spinal anesthesia [CITATION_1] and that sensory level could affect hemodynamic changes. However, despite the possibility of prolonged spinal block by dexmedetomidine, since blocked sensory levels were similar at the end of surgery, the hemodynamic effects induced by blocked levels might have been minimal in the present study.",
